text: View of the Rector's Palace. The rector (in Latin; , ) was an official in the government of the Republic of Ragusa. The holder was the head of the executive powers of Ragusa, part of the Small Council (Consilium minus). The rector was seated at the Rector's Palace. ==Notable citizens of Ragusa== ==List== *Marco Mauroceno (fl. 1343) ==References== ==Sources== * * * Category:Republic of Ragusa Category:Chancellors (government)
